// sourcemap property in tsconfig is useful for debugging typescripts projects like normal we cant see ts files in dev tools if we make sourcemap : true then 
// we can see ts files and also keep debugger

// OUTDIR, ROOTDIR 

// WHAT OUTDIR WILL DO 
// if we give outdir : './dist' the compiler will create js files in dist folder 
// if we give rootdir : './src' only ts files inside src will be consider for compilation

//strict mode 

//noimplicitany : true it will make sure that in ts file all function parameters should have type assignment. if there is no type assignment it will throw
// error no parameter data implicitly has any types 

//important extensions
//prettier
//eslint